# Master Pool — All Generated Bullets

> This file is the reusable bullet pool for all future role-tailored CV variants.
> Every bullet LEAP has generated lives here, tagged by theme.
> The Vanilla CV is built by selecting a subset of these bullets that read as a coherent profile.
> Per-JD variants pull from this pool by tag.
>
> **Anonymization Log lives in `Notes.md`, not here, so this file is safe to share.**

---

## Tagging convention

Every bullet starts with backtick-quoted tags. Standard tags:

| Tag | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `#strategy` | Strategy work — corporate, business unit, product, growth |
| `#operations` | Operating model, process, ways-of-working |
| `#growth` | Revenue, market expansion, new product launches |
| `#ai-impact` | AI/GenAI delivery — capability building, AI-first transformation, AI tooling |
| `#leadership` | Team leadership, hiring, scaling teams |
| `#people-development` | Mentoring, coaching, training (often LIFT-sourced theme) |
| `#transformation` | Large-scale change programs |
| `#client-counselor` | C-suite trust, executive advisory |
| `#technical` | Hands-on engineering or quantitative depth |
| `#product` | Product management, roadmap, prioritization |
| `#international` | Cross-border / multi-country delivery |
| `#publicly-disclosed` | Engagement where the client is publicly disclosed; safe to name |

Custom tags allowed (e.g., `#fintech`, `#regulated`, `#b2b-saas`). Document additions in `Notes.md`.

---

## How to use this file

When tailoring a CV for a specific JD:
1. Identify the JD's top themes (e.g., "AI adoption", "regional enablement", "sales-team restructuring").
2. Filter this file by relevant tags.
3. Within each role, pick the top 4–6 bullets that hit the JD's themes hardest.
4. Reorder within the role from highest-relevance to lowest.

A bullet marked `*(Featured)*` is the version currently used in the Vanilla CV.

